;\n&gt; &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; If he established DLS with the expectation that it becomes=\r\n a success or &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; 10,000 people join it or some such thing, then it w=\r\nould become an &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; ignorant action, i.e. action with attachment. If h=\r\ne did the action &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; completely ready for any outcome and without a s=\r\nense of ownership, and &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; as an instrument of the divine will, then =\r\nit is neither &quot;worldly&quot; nor &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; binding nor ignorant. The problem is =\r\nnot &quot;actions&quot;, but actions with &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; attachment and a sense of ownersh=\r\nip, i.e. actions driven by the will and &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; agenda of a limited ego.&lt;=\r\nbr&gt;\n&gt; &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; Actions should not be spoken ill of like this. Detached =\r\naction is a &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; *sacred duty* of every being. Gods and rishis came ba=\r\nck again and again &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; to earth to engage in detached action.&lt;br&gt;\n&gt=\r\n; &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; *        *        *&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; If &quot;the atman is entirel=\r\ny opposed to action&quot;, then why is atman (Self) &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; even allowing acti=\r\non? Why doesn&#39;t it simply halt everything? Or, is all &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; the action =\r\nhappening outside of atman? Is there anything outside of &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; atman at=\r\n all?&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; Some buddhist philosophies coined the term anatman=\r\n (non-Self) to &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; describe transient things. But, in Vedic philosoph=\r\ny, there is no &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; anatman. All that is is atman (Self). Ocean is per=\r\nmanent and still, but &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; ripples that arise in it are transient and =\r\nmoving. But ripples are part &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; of ocean only and you do not start l=\r\nabeling ripples as &quot;non-ocean&quot;.&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; Atman or Purusha or Shiv=\r\na is the potential energy of this cosmos, while &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; Maya or Prakriti =\r\nor Shakti is the kinetic energy of this cosmos. Shiva &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; and Shakti =\r\nare seen as different entities by some people, but rishis &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; have de=\r\nclared their oneness. Potential energy becomes kinetic energy and &lt;br&gt;\n&gt;=\r\n vice versa.&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; Atman is the still ocean and Maya is the fo=\r\nrce (kinetic) that gives rise &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; to moving ripples on the surface. A=\r\n ripple that exerts itself to move in &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; a particular way keeps coll=\r\niding with the force and keeps moving hither &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; and tither in a chao=\r\ntic way for a very long time. A ripple that does not &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; exert itself=\r\n and moves smoothly as dictated by the force will eventually &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; grin=\r\nd to a halt and cease to exist as a ripple on the surface. It then &lt;br&gt;\n&gt=\r\n; becomes part of the still ocean. If a ripple exerts itself to become &lt;br&gt;=\r\n\n&gt; still, it may even take longer to become still. What prolongs a rippl=\r\ne &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; is not movement but resisting the direction given by the force =\r\nand &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; exerting to move in a particular way (or even exerting to bec=\r\nome still). &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; A ripple that surrenders to the force will ride the c=\r\nourse and die down &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; faster.&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; Contemplate the ima=\r\ngery I presented above regarding Atman and Maya, &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; ignorant/egoisti=\r\nc action and detached action! It is very apt.&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; *        *=\r\n        *&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; In not-so-distant past, sannyasins remained in=\r\n ashrams and isolated &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; themselves from society and did their sadha=\r\nna. Swami Vivekananda started &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; a new trend.&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; A s=\r\nannyasin renounces expectation of things from people stuck in &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; tra=\r\nnsient material world and does not depend on anyone. But he may still &lt;br&gt;\n=\r\n&gt; *give* basic material things to those hapless people stuck in transien=\r\nt &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; material world! For example, Swami Vivekananda and his brother =\r\nmonks &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; went to places struck by plague, floods, droughts, cyclones=\r\n etc and &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; served people. They provided food, medicines etc (instea=\r\nd of lecturing &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; that body is a transient illusion and one should s=\r\ntop worrying about its &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; welfare!) and also did construction work. =\r\nThey ignored the welfare of &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; their own bodies, put themselves at r=\r\nisk and overcame maya personally. &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; But they served those still stu=\r\nck in maya without looking down upon them &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; or their needs or maya =\r\nthat trapped them! Those who wanted food got &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; food, those who want=\r\ned medicines got medicines and those who wanted &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; books got books. =\r\nRenunciation means you do not expect anything from &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; anyone and acc=\r\nept whatever comes to you naturally. It does not &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; necessarily mean=\r\n rejecting or ignoring others. Overcoming maya does not &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; require b=\r\nelittling maya or belittling those still stuck in maya.&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; =\r\nThe trend started by Swami Vivekananda was continued by Swami Sivananda. &lt;b=\r\nr&gt;\n&gt; For that reason, it is a bit weird to see him talking so ill of act=\r\nion! &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; He was obviously trying to inspire a specific group of peopl=\r\ne for a &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; specific body of work. These words are neither universal =\r\nnor do they &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; reflect his tremendous wisdom I have seen elsewhere!&lt;=\r\nbr&gt;\n&gt; &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; *        *        *&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; All this intellec=\r\ntual discussion may be satisfying to some, but the &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; quote from Swa=\r\nmi Brahmanananda in the other mail is very apt: &quot;You have &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; been on=\r\nly hearing of all these spiritual things. Now realise them. You &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; h=\r\nave done enough study and reasoning. Now do some spiritual practice. &lt;br&gt;\n&=\r\ngt; First take up that aspect of God which appeals to you most. Follow your=\r\n &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; own path of Sadhana. When you realise God through it, you will f=\r\neel the &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; joy of realising Him also in other aspects and through ot=\r\nher paths.&quot;&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; According to Ramakrishna, Swami Brahmananda =\r\nwas a gopala who accompanied &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; Lord Krishna in a previous life. His=\r\n words are simple, pragmatic and &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; powerful.&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; I w=\r\nant this forum to facilitate exchange of Vedic knowledge (and I will &lt;br&gt;\n&=\r\ngt; also be contributing, though in spurts). But I want more that this foru=\r\nm &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; should inspire people to do sadhana and find God. In the end, t=\r\nhat is &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; what matters.&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; Best regards,&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; Na=\r\nrasimha&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; ----------------------------------------------------------=\r\n&lt;br&gt;\n&gt;    Free Jyotish Software, Free Jyotish Lessons, Jyotish Writings,=\r\n&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &quot;Do It Yourself&quot; ritual manuals for short Homam and Pitri Tarpana=\r\n:&lt;br&gt;&lt;span&gt;\n&gt;                    &lt;a target=3D&quot;_blank&quot; href=3D&quot;http://www=\r\n.VedicAstrologer.org&quot;&gt;http://www.VedicAstrologer.org&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span&gt;\n&=\r\ngt;       Films that make a difference: &lt;a target=3D&quot;_blank&quot; href=3D&quot;http:/=\r\n/SaraswatiFilms.org&quot;&gt;http://SaraswatiFilms.org&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span&gt;\n&gt;   =\r\n    Spirituality: &lt;a target=3D&quot;_blank&quot; href=3D&quot;http://groups.yahoo.com/grou=\r\np/vedic-wisdom&quot;&gt;http://groups.yahoo.com/group/v